act with a Buyer."}, "usage" : {"en": "According to the definition of <a href= \"https:\/\/eur-lex.europa.eu\/eli\/reg\/2024\/2509\/oj\/eng#d1e2310-1-1\">Article 2 <\/a> a contractor is an economic operator with whom a public contract has been signed. Additionally an economic operator is defined as 'any natural or legal person, including a public entity, or a group of such persons, who offers to supply products, execute works or provide services or supply immovable property'.\r\n\r\n"}, "ap-label-en" : {"en": "Contractor"}, "definition" : {"en": "The Role of an Agent  that has signed a Contract with a Buyer."}, "label" : {"en": "Contractor"}},
"name": "Contractor"
}
